VSponsored by SPIC-MACAY, renowned exponent of carnatic music, M.K.S. Siva of Mambalam gave a nadaswaram recital last Tuesday morning for the benefit of the young pupils of Sri Prakash Vidya Niketan.A performer of wide repute in and outside the country (he has performed in countries like France, USA, Australia, Srilanka and the UK) and who stands ranked as one of the top among A-grade artistes of AIR, started his recital with a brief aalapana of Abhogi and played the varnam in it striking a resonantly scintillating note.Keeping up the tenor, fervour and tempo, he made it an elatedly nutrimental treat playingVaatapiganapathim(Hamsadhvani) concluded with swaram,Endaromahanubhavulu(Sri) preluded with aesthetic aalapana,Kondalalonelakonnaof Annamayya (Hindolam) and expansive expatiation ofNagumomuganaleni(Abheri). The vibrating Thani on dolu by P.R.M. Venkatesh and P. Arunachalam replete with all intricate nuances of laya was thrilling. Siva then played Sankara Naadasareera from the feature filmSankarabharanamand national songVandemaatharambefore concluding his two hour recital with a thillana.K. Durgaprasad on another naadaswaram, P. Kiran Kumar and Omprakash marking the thalam and sruthi lent excellent support. Coordinator of the local chapter of the SPIC-MACAY, S. Vijayakumar, in association with the chief administrative officer J. Malini and the principal of the Vidya Nikethan, Nafeesa Begum, diligently organised the concert.
